
# Configuring providers

In the configuration json file, there is a `providers` section where you can list all providers you wish to use.

Each provider has an API key, a default model name, a URL, and a type.

Currently, we only support


# configuration for Groq

```json

{
  "providers": {
    "groq": {
      "api_key": "PASTE-YOUR-GROQ-KEY-HERE",
      "model": "qwen/qwen3-32b",
      "api_url": "https://api.groq.com/openai/v1/chat/completions",
      "type": "openai"
    }

}
```


# Configuration for Anthropic

{
  "providers": {
    "anthropic": {
      "api_key": "PASTE-YOUR-KEY-HERE",
      "model": "claude-sonnet-4-20250514",
      "api_url": "https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages",
      "type": "anthropic"
    },
    "groq": {
      "api_key": "PASTE-YOUR-GROQ-KEY-HERE",
      "model": "qwen/qwen3-32b",
      "api_url": "https://api.groq.com/openai/v1/chat/completions",
      "type": "openai"
    },
    "lmstudio": {
      "api_key": "",
      "model": "local-model",
      "api_url": "http://localhost:1234/v1/chat/completions",
      "type": "openai"
    }
  },
  "mcp_servers": {
    "r2mcp": {
      "type": "stdio",
      "command": "r2pm",
      "args": [
        "-r",
        "r2mcp"
      ]
    },
    "example_http": {
      "type": "http",
      "url": "http://localhost:8080/mcp"
    }
  },
  "debug": true
}